The paper focuses on modeling conversations on social media, specifically on Reddit, using a graph-structured bidirectional LSTM. This involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with predicting the popularity of comments, which could fall under the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. The use of a graph-structured LSTM also suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with analyzing and improving the performance of the proposed model, which could fall under the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category.
